Electrical Principles
fields.description: Demonstrate knowledge and understanding of electrical principles, including Ohm's law, Kirchhoff's laws, AC/DC theory, power calculations, and electromagnetic principles.

fields.title: Electrical Drawings and Diagrams
fields.description: Interpret and produce electrical drawings, circuit diagrams, wiring diagrams, and schematic representations used in electrical installations.

fields.title: Electrical Machines and Motors
fields.description: Demonstrate knowledge of electrical machines including transformers, DC motors and generators, AC motors, and motor control systems.

fields.title: Electrical Protection Systems
fields.description: Understand electrical protection devices, earth fault protection, overcurrent protection, and lightning protection systems.

fields.title: Electrical Regulations and Standards
fields.description: Demonstrate knowledge of SANS 10142, Occupational Health and Safety Act, Electrical Installation Regulations, and relevant codes of practice.

fields.title: Electronics Fundamentals
fields.description: Understand basic electronics including semiconductors, rectifiers, transistors, integrated circuits, and electronic control systems.

fields.title: Programmable Logic Controllers
fields.description: Demonstrate knowledge of PLC hardware, programming languages, ladder logic, and industrial automation applications.

fields.title: Three Phase Systems
fields.description: Understand three-phase power systems, star and delta connections, power factor correction, and three-phase motor theory.

fields.title: Install Electrical Wiring Systems
fields.description: Install conduit systems, trunking, cable trays, and various wiring methods in accordance with regulations.

fields.title: Install Distribution Boards and Consumer Units
fields.description: Install and wire distribution boards, consumer units, circuit breakers, and protection devices.

fields.title: Install Electrical Equipment and Accessories
fields.description: Install switches, socket outlets, light fittings, and electrical accessories in various installation environments.

fields.title: Install and Connect Motors
fields.description: Install, connect and commission single-phase and three-phase motors, including motor starters and control circuits.

fields.title: Test and Commission Electrical Installations
fields.description: Perform insulation resistance tests, earth continuity tests, polarity tests, and issue Certificates of Compliance.

fields.title: Fault Finding and Repairs
fields.description: Diagnose electrical faults using systematic troubleshooting methods and repair or replace faulty components.

fields.title: Install Industrial Control Systems
fields.description: Install and wire industrial control panels, motor control centres, and automated control systems.

fields.title: PLC Installation and Programming
fields.description: Install PLC systems, write and test ladder logic programs, and commission automated control systems.

fields.title: Workplace Electrical Safety
fields.description: Demonstrate safe working practices in electrical environments, including lockout/tagout procedures and PPE usage.

fields.title: Residential Electrical Installations
fields.description: Gain workplace experience in residential electrical installations including houses, apartments, and small buildings.

fields.title: Commercial Electrical Installations
fields.description: Gain workplace experience in commercial electrical installations including offices, shops, and commercial buildings.

fields.title: Industrial Electrical Systems
fields.description: Gain workplace experience in industrial electrical systems including factories, plants, and heavy machinery.

fields.title: Electrical Maintenance
fields.description: Perform preventive and corrective maintenance on electrical installations and equipment in workplace settings.

fields.title: Customer Service and Documentation
fields.description: Interact professionally with customers, complete job cards, maintain records, and prepare compliance documentation.
